about.summary: Functions and classes for spatial resampling to use with the 'rsample' package, such as spatial cross-validation (Brenning, 2012) <doi:10.1109/IGARSS.2012.6352393>. The scope of 'rsample' and 'spatialsample' is to provide the basic building blocks for creating and analyzing resamples of a spatial data set, but neither package includes functions for modeling or computing statistics. The resampled spatial data sets created by 'spatialsample' do not contain much overhead in memory.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.6.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spatialsample
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/spatialsample_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/spatialsample/spatialsample_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 22a6e68e2c83bc389591c75745e1197b3c631ee8dd9d9d3d01d60c49ae89675f

build:
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/
  missing_dso_whitelist:
    - '*/R.dll'        # [win]
    - '*/Rblas.dll'    # [win]
    - '*/Rlapack.dll'  # [win]
  # Checking windows to see if it passes. Uncomment the line if it fails.
  # skip: true  # [win]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}          # [not win]
    - {{ stdlib('c') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}    # [win]
    - {{ stdlib('m2w64_c') }}      # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cpp11
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=1.0.0
    - r-rsample >=1.1.1
    - r-sf >=1.0_9
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-units
    - r-vctrs >=0.3.6
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cpp11
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang >=1.0.0
    - r-rsample >=1.1.1
    - r-sf >=1.0_9
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-units
    - r-vctrs >=0.3.6

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('spatialsample')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('spatialsample')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://spatialsample.tidymodels.org
  dev_url: https://github.com/tidymodels/spatialsample
  license: MIT
  summary: Functions and classes for spatial resampling to use with the 'rsample' package, such as spatial cross-validation (Brenning, 2012) <doi:10.1109/IGARSS.2012.6352393>. The scope of 'rsample' and 'spatialsample' is to provide the basic building blocks for creating and analyzing resamples of a spatial data set, but
    neither package includes functions for modeling or computing statistics. The resampled spatial data sets created by 'spatialsample' do not contain much overhead in memory.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
